API Server
=================================

Deploy
---------------
To deploy apiserver do a git clone and run 

./activator start

This will download all the dependencies and start apiserver on port 9000


Details
---------------

Questions API tested and deployed in prod. Routes working as of now are: 
1) GET v1/questions  - to perform query. returns a list of questions
2) POST v1/questions - to add question. returns the saved question. 
3) GET v1/questions/1234455 - returns a single question with id 1234455


1) GET v1/questions

sample usage: 
> http://52.11.12.87:9000/v1/questions
> http://52.11.12.87:9000/v1/questions?method=generic&q={isAnonymous:false}&sort={createdAt:-1}&rows=10&start=0
> http://52.11.12.87:9000/v1/questions?method=generic&q={isAnonymous:false}

default values: 
> method = "generic"
> q = "{isAnonymous:false}"
> sort = "{createdAt:-1}"
> start = 0;
> rows = 10;

2) POST v1/questions

sample usage:
curl -i -H "Accept: application/json" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -X POST -d '{ "statement":"Who is better?", "tags": [ { "name":"music" }, { "name":"progressive rock" } ], "answers": [ { "statement":"Pink Floyd" }, { "statement":"Porcupine Tree" } ], "createdBy": { "id":"-1", "name":"Ashutosh Mishra" } }' http://52.11.12.87:9000/v1/questions

json structure (exhaustive options):
(NOTE: not all fields are compulsory)

{
    "statement":"Who is better?",         //Compulsory field
    "tags":
    [
        {
            "name":"comedian"
        },
        {
           "name":"tv"
        }
    ],
    "answers":
    [
        {
            "statement":"Hugh Laurie"         //Compulsory field
        },
        {
            "statement":"Stephen Fry"         //Compulsory field
        }
    ],
    "createdBy":
    {
        "id":"-1",                                //Compulsory field 
// RESERVING id=-1 FOR ADMIN USE (so use this for all questions for now)
        "name":"Ashutosh Mishra"         //Compulsory field
        "screenName":"ashutoshdtu"
        "email":"ashutosh@podkart.com"
    }
}